      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hilton%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The Chase Cobblestone Farmhouse and Curtis-Crumb Farm are listed on the National Register of Historic Places.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        4
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hilton%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Salmon Creek, a direct tributary of Lake Ontario, flows eastward through the south side of Hilton.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        15
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hilton%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "New York State Route 18 cuts through Hilton, connecting the village to nearby towns.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
